<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2891] bug in GroovyCategorySupport - infinite loop</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2891</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;GroovyCategorySupport has bug in methods prioritization logic, that can lead to infinite loop.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please try this snippet in groovy 1.6-beta-2:&lt;br/&gt;
groovy -e &quot;org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.GroovyCategorySupport.use(groovy.servlet.ServletCategory, &lt;/p&gt;
{println &apos;Hello&apos;}
&lt;p&gt;)&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just tried it in specified version of Groovy, downloaded from &lt;a href=&quot;http://build.canoo.com/groovy/artifacts/20080603122913/dist/groovy-binary-1.6-beta-2-SNAPSHOT.zip&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.canoo.com/groovy/artifacts/20080603122913/dist/groovy-binary-1.6-beta-2-SNAPSHOT.zip&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Groovy hangs up.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The solution is quite simple (see patch).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
